WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:27.630 align:middle line:90%


00:00:27.630 --> 00:00:31.290 align:middle line:10%
>> Are you really doing what
you want to do with your life?

00:00:31.290 --> 00:00:33.720 align:middle line:10%
Has it ever occurred to
you that you may have

00:00:33.720 --> 00:00:36.930 align:middle line:10%
a special calling or passion?

00:00:36.930 --> 00:00:40.790 align:middle line:10%
I am Marilyn McGuire and
this is the Wisdom Channel.

00:00:40.790 --> 00:00:44.730 align:middle line:10%
We are talking today with
Justine and Michael Toms,

00:00:44.730 --> 00:00:48.570 align:middle line:10%
co-authors of the
book, "True Work--

00:00:48.570 --> 00:00:52.390 align:middle line:10%
The Sacred Dimension
of Earning a Living."

00:00:52.390 --> 00:00:55.650 align:middle line:84%
Justine, welcome
to Wisdom Channel.

00:00:55.650 --> 00:00:57.050 align:middle line:90%
>> So good to be here, Marilyn.

00:00:57.050 --> 00:00:57.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:00:57.850 --> 00:01:00.150 align:middle line:10%
Can you tell us
what is true work?

00:01:00.150 --> 00:01:03.990 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, true work is really
listening to your inner voice

00:01:03.990 --> 00:01:07.890 align:middle line:10%
and following your passion,
finding that which has meaning

00:01:07.890 --> 00:01:12.100 align:middle line:10%
for you, and manifesting
that in the world.

00:01:12.100 --> 00:01:16.060 align:middle line:84%
Whether you earn a living with
it or not is another question.

00:01:16.060 --> 00:01:18.420 align:middle line:84%
But we really need
to follow our passion

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:23.880 align:middle line:84%
and find our gifts that we are
here to give, and to give them.

00:01:23.880 --> 00:01:27.630 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, from your point of
view, how has your life--

00:01:27.630 --> 00:01:29.310 align:middle line:10%
how have you followed
your passion,

00:01:29.310 --> 00:01:31.870 align:middle line:10%
or have you discovered your
passion, is the main thing.

00:01:31.870 --> 00:01:33.900 align:middle line:10%
And then when you
do, how do you know

00:01:33.900 --> 00:01:36.390 align:middle line:10%
it's really your passion
and really your service?

00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:37.715 align:middle line:90%
And how do you follow it?

00:01:37.715 --> 00:01:40.340 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, you know, for me-- and
it's going to be different from

00:01:40.340 --> 00:01:41.220 align:middle line:90%
Michael--

00:01:41.220 --> 00:01:47.550 align:middle line:84%
but for me, it came rather
slowly and unfolded.

00:01:47.550 --> 00:01:50.760 align:middle line:84%
But when Michael and
I first got together,

00:01:50.760 --> 00:01:55.140 align:middle line:84%
we started going to all
these seminars and workshops

00:01:55.140 --> 00:02:00.030 align:middle line:84%
about new thought and new
ideas of looking at the world.

00:02:00.030 --> 00:02:01.740 align:middle line:90%
And we got so excited about it.

00:02:01.740 --> 00:02:05.670 align:middle line:84%
We decided that we would like
to do something in the media.

00:02:05.670 --> 00:02:07.420 align:middle line:10%
Because none of
it at that time--

00:02:07.420 --> 00:02:09.539 align:middle line:10%
this was more than
25 years ago--

00:02:09.539 --> 00:02:15.030 align:middle line:10%
was appearing in the media about
meditation or holistic health

00:02:15.030 --> 00:02:20.520 align:middle line:10%
or alternative health,
nothing about the way babies

00:02:20.520 --> 00:02:22.440 align:middle line:10%
are born, like in
birthing rooms.

00:02:22.440 --> 00:02:28.550 align:middle line:84%
And everything was like in
like an emergency in a surgery

00:02:28.550 --> 00:02:29.970 align:middle line:90%
or something.

00:02:29.970 --> 00:02:33.510 align:middle line:84%
So all of these new ideas were
coming in and we got so excited

00:02:33.510 --> 00:02:36.850 align:middle line:84%
we decided to start
something called--

00:02:36.850 --> 00:02:37.650 align:middle line:90%
>> 25 years ago?

00:02:37.650 --> 00:02:38.450 align:middle line:90%
>> 25 years ago.

00:02:38.450 --> 00:02:39.840 align:middle line:90%
And it's called New Dimensions.

00:02:39.840 --> 00:02:43.548 align:middle line:84%
And it became a radio program,
which has now aired all over

00:02:43.548 --> 00:02:45.840 align:middle line:84%
the world-- all over the
United States and now all over

00:02:45.840 --> 00:02:46.640 align:middle line:90%
the world--

00:02:46.640 --> 00:02:48.790 align:middle line:90%
talking about these ideas.

00:02:48.790 --> 00:02:52.620 align:middle line:84%
So we just started by being
excited about the ideas

00:02:52.620 --> 00:02:55.230 align:middle line:84%
and just starting with
what we called baby steps

00:02:55.230 --> 00:02:57.660 align:middle line:90%
and just started to do it.

00:02:57.660 --> 00:03:01.050 align:middle line:90%
Just held some lectures.

00:03:01.050 --> 00:03:05.040 align:middle line:84%
And out of the lectures came
an invitation to do radio.

00:03:05.040 --> 00:03:07.740 align:middle line:90%
And then it just kept unfolding.

00:03:07.740 --> 00:03:12.420 align:middle line:84%
And for me, it's been
a lifelong learning.

00:03:12.420 --> 00:03:14.430 align:middle line:84%
It's been something
that has kept

00:03:14.430 --> 00:03:18.420 align:middle line:90%
me interested for 25 years.

00:03:18.420 --> 00:03:20.550 align:middle line:90%
And that's what true work is.

00:03:20.550 --> 00:03:23.880 align:middle line:84%
We didn't go into it
for earning a living.

00:03:23.880 --> 00:03:27.630 align:middle line:84%
We didn't even think about that
until it just kept working.

00:03:27.630 --> 00:03:30.060 align:middle line:84%
We would subsidize it
for many, many years.

00:03:30.060 --> 00:03:34.540 align:middle line:84%
And it was an all volunteer
organization for many years.

00:03:34.540 --> 00:03:38.700 align:middle line:84%
And then as we just kept
doing it with our enthusiasm,

00:03:38.700 --> 00:03:41.490 align:middle line:84%
with giving it
attention, it just

00:03:41.490 --> 00:03:45.450 align:middle line:84%
developed into something
that now, actually,

00:03:45.450 --> 00:03:46.980 align:middle line:90%
is full time for us.

00:03:46.980 --> 00:03:49.230 align:middle line:10%
>> I want to come back to
talking about New Dimensions

00:03:49.230 --> 00:03:50.030 align:middle line:10%
radio.

00:03:50.030 --> 00:03:51.690 align:middle line:90%
But you mentioned baby steps.

00:03:51.690 --> 00:03:53.820 align:middle line:90%
Can you explain?

00:03:53.820 --> 00:03:55.860 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think it's
really-- you know,

00:03:55.860 --> 00:04:00.330 align:middle line:84%
we have to start with
something that's close to us.

00:04:00.330 --> 00:04:03.090 align:middle line:84%
Because when we are
following our passion

00:04:03.090 --> 00:04:05.750 align:middle line:84%
or following that
inner voice, at first

00:04:05.750 --> 00:04:07.480 align:middle line:90%
it might be a small voice.

00:04:07.480 --> 00:04:09.960 align:middle line:84%
And we might say, oh, I
don't know if I can do it.

00:04:09.960 --> 00:04:12.390 align:middle line:10%
Our vision might be large.

00:04:12.390 --> 00:04:14.940 align:middle line:90%
How do you, how do you start it?

00:04:14.940 --> 00:04:18.750 align:middle line:84%
Well, you start it with
first, what is close to us.

00:04:18.750 --> 00:04:23.520 align:middle line:84%
You start with maybe talking
about it with your friends who

00:04:23.520 --> 00:04:24.850 align:middle line:90%
are very supportive.

00:04:24.850 --> 00:04:27.420 align:middle line:84%
And it's important to have
friends who are supportive,

00:04:27.420 --> 00:04:30.330 align:middle line:84%
who support you in
all of your fullness.

00:04:30.330 --> 00:04:32.340 align:middle line:84%
So to start off with
something like that.

00:04:32.340 --> 00:04:34.835 align:middle line:84%
And maybe like the way we
started New Dimensions,

00:04:34.835 --> 00:04:36.460 align:middle line:84%
we said, well, what
are we going to do.

00:04:36.460 --> 00:04:39.330 align:middle line:84%
We rented a space
in the local church.

00:04:39.330 --> 00:04:41.320 align:middle line:84%
And we invited some
people to speak.

00:04:41.320 --> 00:04:43.920 align:middle line:84%
And we put a little
ad in the newspaper.

00:04:43.920 --> 00:04:44.910 align:middle line:90%
And people came.

00:04:44.910 --> 00:04:47.760 align:middle line:84%
And we had a little shoe
box to collect some,

00:04:47.760 --> 00:04:49.530 align:middle line:90%
I think $3 at the door.

00:04:49.530 --> 00:04:51.660 align:middle line:10%
And we had a little
mailing list that they

00:04:51.660 --> 00:04:53.160 align:middle line:10%
want to know about more.

00:04:53.160 --> 00:04:54.480 align:middle line:90%
Now those are baby steps.

00:04:54.480 --> 00:04:58.440 align:middle line:84%
Now that mailing list of
those first maybe 25 people

00:04:58.440 --> 00:05:00.870 align:middle line:84%
that came to that
first lecture has

00:05:00.870 --> 00:05:04.620 align:middle line:84%
developed into 60,000
name mailing list

00:05:04.620 --> 00:05:06.570 align:middle line:90%
that's kept on computer now.

00:05:06.570 --> 00:05:08.970 align:middle line:84%
Well, if you had
thought about that, how

00:05:08.970 --> 00:05:12.790 align:middle line:84%
are we going to get 60,000
names on a computer at first,

00:05:12.790 --> 00:05:14.580 align:middle line:90%
it would just stop you.

00:05:14.580 --> 00:05:18.780 align:middle line:10%
But if you say, oh, we
just invite a few people

00:05:18.780 --> 00:05:21.400 align:middle line:10%
and we build from that,
and you build from that,

00:05:21.400 --> 00:05:22.500 align:middle line:10%
and those are baby steps.

00:05:22.500 --> 00:05:26.670 align:middle line:10%
Those little steps that we
talk about that are connected,

00:05:26.670 --> 00:05:31.380 align:middle line:10%
one on the other, the next step
will lead you to the next step.

00:05:31.380 --> 00:05:32.360 align:middle line:90%
>> That's fascinating.

00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:35.280 align:middle line:84%
And what comes to
mind for me is,

00:05:35.280 --> 00:05:38.200 align:middle line:84%
in following your
passion along the way,

00:05:38.200 --> 00:05:40.005 align:middle line:84%
do you have a goal
out there in mind,

00:05:40.005 --> 00:05:43.950 align:middle line:84%
or are you just being
led by your passion

00:05:43.950 --> 00:05:47.490 align:middle line:84%
to what will become a goal
that might surprise you

00:05:47.490 --> 00:05:48.720 align:middle line:90%
when it comes?

00:05:48.720 --> 00:05:51.130 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, that's
a great question,

00:05:51.130 --> 00:05:53.040 align:middle line:90%
because it's about the end.

00:05:53.040 --> 00:05:53.960 align:middle line:90%
There is a goal.

00:05:53.960 --> 00:05:55.540 align:middle line:90%
There's an overall vision.

00:05:55.540 --> 00:05:59.940 align:middle line:84%
But it's very, very
important to hold it loosely.

00:05:59.940 --> 00:06:05.130 align:middle line:84%
Because it allows for what
we call magic to happen.

00:06:05.130 --> 00:06:08.430 align:middle line:84%
And when we talk
about magic, it's

00:06:08.430 --> 00:06:13.300 align:middle line:84%
more like when you are really
energized by your vision,

00:06:13.300 --> 00:06:19.020 align:middle line:84%
then it allows the
unexpected to come in.

00:06:19.020 --> 00:06:22.320 align:middle line:84%
And if you hold your
vision so rigidly

00:06:22.320 --> 00:06:24.180 align:middle line:84%
that it's just going
to be this way,

00:06:24.180 --> 00:06:27.800 align:middle line:84%
then that unexpected
can't really come.

00:06:27.800 --> 00:06:30.680 align:middle line:10%
So you need to hold it loosely.

00:06:30.680 --> 00:06:32.480 align:middle line:10%
Let it flow.

00:06:32.480 --> 00:06:36.050 align:middle line:10%
But you have an
overall vision or goal.

00:06:36.050 --> 00:06:40.160 align:middle line:84%
But let it, let it have
room to move and to breathe

00:06:40.160 --> 00:06:41.700 align:middle line:90%
and to grow.

00:06:41.700 --> 00:06:46.160 align:middle line:84%
If we had imagined New
Dimensions as it is now,

00:06:46.160 --> 00:06:50.030 align:middle line:84%
in the very beginning, well,
it was beyond our imagination

00:06:50.030 --> 00:06:52.640 align:middle line:84%
that we would be
worldwide broadcasting.

00:06:52.640 --> 00:06:55.820 align:middle line:84%
We knew overall that
we wanted to talk

00:06:55.820 --> 00:07:01.220 align:middle line:84%
about life-enhancing,
empowering visions in the world

00:07:01.220 --> 00:07:04.560 align:middle line:84%
and bring people on who
were following this path.

00:07:04.560 --> 00:07:08.300 align:middle line:84%
But other than that, we
really held it loosely.

00:07:08.300 --> 00:07:11.840 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, today, after
25 years of this,

00:07:11.840 --> 00:07:15.620 align:middle line:84%
can you describe New Dimensions
radio to those people who may

00:07:15.620 --> 00:07:16.830 align:middle line:90%
not know about it?

00:07:16.830 --> 00:07:17.630 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh I'd love to.

00:07:17.630 --> 00:07:20.150 align:middle line:84%
Well, we're a weekly
program that's

00:07:20.150 --> 00:07:23.570 align:middle line:84%
on about 300 stations
across the United States.

00:07:23.570 --> 00:07:28.040 align:middle line:84%
And it airs on shortwave out of
Europe and Australia and Costa

00:07:28.040 --> 00:07:29.330 align:middle line:90%
Rica.

00:07:29.330 --> 00:07:30.140 align:middle line:90%
>> Amazing.

00:07:30.140 --> 00:07:34.310 align:middle line:10%
>> And every week we invite
someone on who is manifesting

00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:39.410 align:middle line:10%
some positive vision in
the world, something--

00:07:39.410 --> 00:07:43.580 align:middle line:10%
and it could be about anything
from health to psychology,

00:07:43.580 --> 00:07:47.660 align:middle line:10%
from spirituality to, from
I like to say from birthing

00:07:47.660 --> 00:07:50.120 align:middle line:10%
babies to going out into space.

00:07:50.120 --> 00:07:52.400 align:middle line:84%
And it's people who
are doing something

00:07:52.400 --> 00:07:58.130 align:middle line:84%
in their life that is coming up
with solutions for the future,

00:07:58.130 --> 00:08:02.540 align:middle line:84%
for the betterment of all
life, that enhances our ability

00:08:02.540 --> 00:08:06.200 align:middle line:84%
to be together in community,
that enhances our ability

00:08:06.200 --> 00:08:09.500 align:middle line:84%
to be with ourselves, to
accept and love ourselves,

00:08:09.500 --> 00:08:13.790 align:middle line:84%
to love each other more,
and to work in a better

00:08:13.790 --> 00:08:15.530 align:middle line:90%
environment all the way around.

00:08:15.530 --> 00:08:18.770 align:middle line:84%
>> And you had no idea that
this big thing was coming?

00:08:18.770 --> 00:08:20.150 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, we had no idea.

00:08:20.150 --> 00:08:26.240 align:middle line:84%
We just had this enthusiasm for
the ideas that we were hearing.

00:08:26.240 --> 00:08:29.180 align:middle line:84%
And we just kept following
it, following it.

00:08:29.180 --> 00:08:32.360 align:middle line:10%
>> That's the point, that
following is the baby steps

00:08:32.360 --> 00:08:33.320 align:middle line:10%
leading the way.

00:08:33.320 --> 00:08:34.120 align:middle line:90%
>> That's right.

00:08:34.120 --> 00:08:38.480 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, along the way,
was it always easy going?

00:08:38.480 --> 00:08:39.590 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, Marilyn.

00:08:39.590 --> 00:08:41.360 align:middle line:84%
You know, when you
follow your vision--

00:08:41.360 --> 00:08:44.870 align:middle line:84%
I know that years ago we
did many, many interviews

00:08:44.870 --> 00:08:47.900 align:middle line:84%
with Joseph Campbell,
the famous mythologist.

00:08:47.900 --> 00:08:51.420 align:middle line:84%
And he would often talk
about following your bliss.

00:08:51.420 --> 00:08:54.470 align:middle line:84%
Well, people misinterpret
that thinking it's

00:08:54.470 --> 00:08:56.210 align:middle line:90%
all going to be blissful.

00:08:56.210 --> 00:08:58.220 align:middle line:84%
But he talks about
following your bliss

00:08:58.220 --> 00:09:03.530 align:middle line:84%
as going down, going
to where the shadow

00:09:03.530 --> 00:09:07.400 align:middle line:90%
side is, where the compost is.

00:09:07.400 --> 00:09:09.620 align:middle line:10%
I mean, it's
really, you're going

00:09:09.620 --> 00:09:12.830 align:middle line:10%
to learn a lot of
lessons on this path.

00:09:12.830 --> 00:09:15.350 align:middle line:84%
And it's not going
to always feel easy.

00:09:15.350 --> 00:09:18.260 align:middle line:84%
And it's not going to
always feel enjoyable.

00:09:18.260 --> 00:09:22.560 align:middle line:84%
But when you are doing
what has meaning for you,

00:09:22.560 --> 00:09:26.840 align:middle line:84%
you can always revert back
to, oh, why you're doing it.

00:09:26.840 --> 00:09:29.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's important to do
that, to take time out

00:09:29.690 --> 00:09:31.580 align:middle line:90%
to think, why am I doing this.

00:09:31.580 --> 00:09:35.690 align:middle line:10%
When the going gets tough, when
maybe the money isn't coming in

00:09:35.690 --> 00:09:39.320 align:middle line:10%
or maybe all the details
are not working out,

00:09:39.320 --> 00:09:41.750 align:middle line:10%
there are always
going to be details.

00:09:41.750 --> 00:09:45.320 align:middle line:84%
And that's where we have to
learn to be in the present

00:09:45.320 --> 00:09:47.110 align:middle line:90%
and to have a single focus.

00:09:47.110 --> 00:09:49.730 align:middle line:10%
>> So how is it having a
partnership with a husband,

00:09:49.730 --> 00:09:52.280 align:middle line:10%
a husband and wife
team working together?

00:09:52.280 --> 00:09:53.820 align:middle line:10%
>> Well, that's been wonderful.

00:09:53.820 --> 00:09:56.390 align:middle line:84%
I think because
Michael and I, we

00:09:56.390 --> 00:09:58.400 align:middle line:84%
have something that
we're working on that's

00:09:58.400 --> 00:10:00.680 align:middle line:90%
bigger than the two of us.

00:10:00.680 --> 00:10:05.000 align:middle line:84%
And you know, when we
got together, we always

00:10:05.000 --> 00:10:06.500 align:middle line:84%
thought that we
would have children,

00:10:06.500 --> 00:10:09.825 align:middle line:84%
although we both had children
from former relationships.

00:10:09.825 --> 00:10:11.450 align:middle line:10%
We thought that we
would have children.

00:10:11.450 --> 00:10:14.160 align:middle line:10%
And it just kind
of never happened.

00:10:14.160 --> 00:10:16.940 align:middle line:10%
And then through the years,
as we look back on it,

00:10:16.940 --> 00:10:19.310 align:middle line:10%
we realized that
really, about nine

00:10:19.310 --> 00:10:23.360 align:middle line:10%
months after we got together,
we started New Dimensions.

00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:25.670 align:middle line:10%
And here it is going on.

00:10:25.670 --> 00:10:28.020 align:middle line:90%
And now it's grown up.

00:10:28.020 --> 00:10:31.910 align:middle line:84%
And it seems to be
our creation together.

00:10:31.910 --> 00:10:34.990 align:middle line:84%
And it's been a
wonderful creation.

00:10:34.990 --> 00:10:37.280 align:middle line:90%
>> That is very, very touching.

00:10:37.280 --> 00:10:38.860 align:middle line:10%
Thank you, Justine.

00:10:38.860 --> 00:10:43.700 align:middle line:10%
I'm Marilyn McGuire and you are
watching the Wisdom Channel.

