I'd like to introduce
Michael Toms.

00:11:17.533 --> 00:11:18.450 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you, Marilyn.

00:11:18.450 --> 00:11:19.250 align:middle line:90%
Nice to be here.

00:11:19.250 --> 00:11:20.670 align:middle line:90%
>> It is nice to see you.

00:11:20.670 --> 00:11:26.310 align:middle line:84%
Tell me, Justine who said
her feelings about true work.

00:11:26.310 --> 00:11:28.100 align:middle line:84%
I'm sure you must
feel similar to it.

00:11:28.100 --> 00:11:30.840 align:middle line:84%
But since you've
both wrote the book,

00:11:30.840 --> 00:11:34.350 align:middle line:84%
give me, tell us
about your idea.

00:11:34.350 --> 00:11:37.800 align:middle line:10%
>> I think true work is an
expression of our following

00:11:37.800 --> 00:11:40.060 align:middle line:10%
our passion for
the last 25 years.

00:11:40.060 --> 00:11:42.120 align:middle line:10%
And so it reflects
some of the principles

00:11:42.120 --> 00:11:45.360 align:middle line:10%
that we've learned and have put
into practice over those years,

00:11:45.360 --> 00:11:47.760 align:middle line:10%
as well as our
passion is talking

00:11:47.760 --> 00:11:50.132 align:middle line:10%
to other people about
their passion in the work

00:11:50.132 --> 00:11:51.840 align:middle line:10%
that we do on the
radio and the dialogues

00:11:51.840 --> 00:11:53.328 align:middle line:10%
that we have on the radio.

00:11:53.328 --> 00:11:54.870 align:middle line:84%
So we've talked to
many, many people,

00:11:54.870 --> 00:11:56.850 align:middle line:84%
I mean, really
thousands of people,

00:11:56.850 --> 00:11:59.970 align:middle line:84%
over 3,000 people, many of whom
are following their passion.

00:11:59.970 --> 00:12:02.770 align:middle line:84%
And we've picked up a few
pointers along the way.

00:12:02.770 --> 00:12:04.800 align:middle line:84%
So the book is
expressive of not only

00:12:04.800 --> 00:12:07.270 align:middle line:84%
our own grounded
practical experience,

00:12:07.270 --> 00:12:09.390 align:middle line:84%
but the experience
of many others

00:12:09.390 --> 00:12:12.040 align:middle line:84%
about what following
your passion is all about

00:12:12.040 --> 00:12:14.780 align:middle line:90%
and what we call true work.

00:12:14.780 --> 00:12:20.010 align:middle line:84%
>> Following your passion, like
everyone has a mission in life,

00:12:20.010 --> 00:12:22.500 align:middle line:90%
perhaps, that they need to find.

00:12:22.500 --> 00:12:25.710 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think everyone,
particularly in these times

00:12:25.710 --> 00:12:29.430 align:middle line:84%
with this kind of bottom line
business as usual mentality,

00:12:29.430 --> 00:12:32.470 align:middle line:84%
that something is being
trampled in the process.

00:12:32.470 --> 00:12:35.250 align:middle line:84%
And that something essential
is that deep longing

00:12:35.250 --> 00:12:40.200 align:middle line:84%
that all of us have to give our
gifts, to make a contribution,

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:41.590 align:middle line:90%
to be of service.

00:12:41.590 --> 00:12:43.600 align:middle line:90%
I think everyone has that.

00:12:43.600 --> 00:12:46.110 align:middle line:84%
And so it's really important
that we give those gifts.

00:12:46.110 --> 00:12:48.500 align:middle line:84%
Because each of
us is an original.

00:12:48.500 --> 00:12:49.300 align:middle line:90%
We're unique.

00:12:49.300 --> 00:12:51.090 align:middle line:90%
And we have gifts to offer.

00:12:51.090 --> 00:12:55.030 align:middle line:84%
And so as we give them, the
world becomes a better place.

00:12:55.030 --> 00:12:57.075 align:middle line:84%
So this is what I mean by
following your passion.

00:12:57.075 --> 00:12:58.950 align:middle line:84%
It's really important
to follow your passion,

00:12:58.950 --> 00:13:00.615 align:middle line:90%
whatever it may be.

00:13:00.615 --> 00:13:02.490 align:middle line:10%
Well, my passion is
clearly my work, the work

00:13:02.490 --> 00:13:03.612 align:middle line:10%
that I do on the radio.

00:13:03.612 --> 00:13:05.070 align:middle line:84%
But I have other
passions, as well.

00:13:05.070 --> 00:13:07.230 align:middle line:84%
My grandchildren are
a passion for me.

00:13:07.230 --> 00:13:08.610 align:middle line:90%
Birds are a passion for me.

00:13:08.610 --> 00:13:10.678 align:middle line:84%
I have bird feeders all
over around our house.

00:13:10.678 --> 00:13:12.720 align:middle line:84%
And every morning I get
up and go feed the birds.

00:13:12.720 --> 00:13:15.322 align:middle line:84%
And it's a great way
to start the day.

00:13:15.322 --> 00:13:16.530 align:middle line:90%
And so I have other passions.

00:13:16.530 --> 00:13:17.970 align:middle line:90%
Reading is a passion.

00:13:17.970 --> 00:13:18.960 align:middle line:90%
I love books.

00:13:18.960 --> 00:13:21.480 align:middle line:84%
I have 30 or 40 books
by my bed, you know?

00:13:21.480 --> 00:13:23.130 align:middle line:90%
And I'm reading all of them.

00:13:23.130 --> 00:13:24.150 align:middle line:90%
Because I love books.

00:13:24.150 --> 00:13:25.500 align:middle line:90%
And so that's a passion.

00:13:25.500 --> 00:13:28.583 align:middle line:84%
So many of us have,
we all have passions.

00:13:28.583 --> 00:13:30.000 align:middle line:10%
And it's important
to follow them,

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:32.580 align:middle line:10%
to make them a
priority in our life.

00:13:32.580 --> 00:13:35.160 align:middle line:84%
You know, all too often we
get caught in the fast lane

00:13:35.160 --> 00:13:37.200 align:middle line:84%
and all we're
doing is busyness--

00:13:37.200 --> 00:13:38.490 align:middle line:90%
busy, busy, busy.

00:13:38.490 --> 00:13:42.230 align:middle line:84%
We never get in the off
ramp to enjoy our passions.

00:13:42.230 --> 00:13:45.720 align:middle line:84%
And it's only by doing that
that we can really feed our soul

00:13:45.720 --> 00:13:49.740 align:middle line:84%
and nurture our soul and
have real joy in our life.

00:13:49.740 --> 00:13:51.370 align:middle line:90%
>> This sounds very exciting.

00:13:51.370 --> 00:13:54.360 align:middle line:84%
There's also a bit of
a scary aspect to it.

00:13:54.360 --> 00:13:56.730 align:middle line:84%
>> It's exciting because it
comes from that deep place

00:13:56.730 --> 00:14:01.500 align:middle line:84%
in ourselves that is
exciting and is motivational.

00:14:01.500 --> 00:14:02.910 align:middle line:90%
It's energizing.

00:14:02.910 --> 00:14:06.390 align:middle line:84%
And so when we follow our
passion, it is energizing.

00:14:06.390 --> 00:14:07.570 align:middle line:90%
We get joy from it.

00:14:07.570 --> 00:14:08.950 align:middle line:90%
And it's not always easy.

00:14:08.950 --> 00:14:09.750 align:middle line:90%
It's an adventure.

00:14:09.750 --> 00:14:11.610 align:middle line:84%
I mean, it's like
jumping into the abyss.

00:14:11.610 --> 00:14:13.380 align:middle line:90%
We've got to take the leap.

00:14:13.380 --> 00:14:15.300 align:middle line:84%
And we go into the
unknown where we

00:14:15.300 --> 00:14:18.427 align:middle line:84%
have to let go of what we
know and what we are used to.

00:14:18.427 --> 00:14:20.760 align:middle line:84%
And really, that's the place
where creativity can really

00:14:20.760 --> 00:14:23.130 align:middle line:84%
happen because we have
to give up the known.

00:14:23.130 --> 00:14:26.368 align:middle line:84%
So chaos is really a
great place, Marilyn.

00:14:26.368 --> 00:14:27.910 align:middle line:84%
>> I never thought
about it that way.

00:14:27.910 --> 00:14:30.720 align:middle line:84%
I certainly have a
lot of it in my life.

00:14:30.720 --> 00:14:31.720 align:middle line:90%
>> So that's a blessing.

00:14:31.720 --> 00:14:33.220 align:middle line:84%
When we're in chaos,
it's a blessing.

00:14:33.220 --> 00:14:34.020 align:middle line:90%
>> I think it is.

00:14:34.020 --> 00:14:35.470 align:middle line:10%
Ans as Justine
spoke about, I know

00:14:35.470 --> 00:14:37.330 align:middle line:10%
that there are baby
steps along the way,

00:14:37.330 --> 00:14:40.630 align:middle line:10%
as well as a lot
of ups and downs.

00:14:40.630 --> 00:14:44.590 align:middle line:84%
And have there been any
special turning points for you

00:14:44.590 --> 00:14:47.420 align:middle line:90%
along your way?

00:14:47.420 --> 00:14:48.220 align:middle line:10%
>> Absolutely.

00:14:48.220 --> 00:14:48.910 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:14:48.910 --> 00:14:51.310 align:middle line:84%
One of the turning points in
my life was meeting Justine.

00:14:51.310 --> 00:14:51.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh.

00:14:51.850 --> 00:14:53.558 align:middle line:84%
>> That was a major
turning point for me.

00:14:53.558 --> 00:14:58.000 align:middle line:84%
Because I was in the advertising
business before I met Justine.

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.520 align:middle line:84%
And I always knew that
my career in advertising

00:15:00.520 --> 00:15:01.650 align:middle line:90%
would be short term.

00:15:01.650 --> 00:15:02.450 align:middle line:90%
I loved it.

00:15:02.450 --> 00:15:03.250 align:middle line:90%
I enjoyed it.

00:15:03.250 --> 00:15:04.360 align:middle line:90%
I was a great copywriter.

00:15:04.360 --> 00:15:06.160 align:middle line:90%
I loved doing that.

00:15:06.160 --> 00:15:09.430 align:middle line:84%
And yet I knew all the time
this was not my life's work.

00:15:09.430 --> 00:15:11.830 align:middle line:84%
And I knew at some point
I would give it up.

00:15:11.830 --> 00:15:14.140 align:middle line:84%
When I met Justine,
within a couple months

00:15:14.140 --> 00:15:15.630 align:middle line:90%
I was ready to give it up.

00:15:15.630 --> 00:15:16.840 align:middle line:90%
It was time.

00:15:16.840 --> 00:15:19.870 align:middle line:84%
And so I left the
advertising business.

00:15:19.870 --> 00:15:21.970 align:middle line:84%
We bought a camper and
intended to travel around

00:15:21.970 --> 00:15:23.470 align:middle line:90%
the United States for a year.

00:15:23.470 --> 00:15:25.260 align:middle line:90%
We made it for 3 and 1/2 months.

00:15:25.260 --> 00:15:26.260 align:middle line:90%
And it was a great trip.

00:15:26.260 --> 00:15:27.400 align:middle line:90%
It was wonderful.

00:15:27.400 --> 00:15:30.170 align:middle line:84%
And we've been
together ever since.

00:15:30.170 --> 00:15:33.200 align:middle line:84%
But that clearly changed
my life at that point.

00:15:33.200 --> 00:15:34.770 align:middle line:90%
>> That's a wonderful thing.

00:15:34.770 --> 00:15:36.330 align:middle line:90%
This was a very positive thing.

00:15:36.330 --> 00:15:38.550 align:middle line:84%
Had there been other
things that have

00:15:38.550 --> 00:15:42.450 align:middle line:84%
been kind of depressing
to you or made

00:15:42.450 --> 00:15:45.980 align:middle line:84%
you feel that you weren't
on the right path.

00:15:45.980 --> 00:15:49.180 align:middle line:84%
>> There was a situation that
was extremely challenging

00:15:49.180 --> 00:15:49.980 align:middle line:90%
and stressful.

00:15:49.980 --> 00:15:52.890 align:middle line:84%
One of those was when we got
canceled by our main station

00:15:52.890 --> 00:15:54.510 align:middle line:90%
in San Francisco.

00:15:54.510 --> 00:15:57.260 align:middle line:84%
You know, in the '70s, we were
just in Northern California.

00:15:57.260 --> 00:15:59.760 align:middle line:84%
And the station that we were
on, we were on Saturday nights.

00:15:59.760 --> 00:16:01.630 align:middle line:90%
We had a four hour live program.

00:16:01.630 --> 00:16:02.880 align:middle line:90%
We were on for six years.

00:16:02.880 --> 00:16:06.150 align:middle line:84%
We were the most listened
to program on that station

00:16:06.150 --> 00:16:09.120 align:middle line:84%
and most popular program on
Public Radio in the Bay Area.

00:16:09.120 --> 00:16:10.890 align:middle line:90%
And they canceled it.

00:16:10.890 --> 00:16:12.510 align:middle line:84%
Just one day they
said we were gone.

00:16:12.510 --> 00:16:14.470 align:middle line:84%
You know, they were
changing their format.

00:16:14.470 --> 00:16:16.680 align:middle line:84%
And so we were left high
and dry without our station,

00:16:16.680 --> 00:16:19.957 align:middle line:84%
without our audience,
our support.

00:16:19.957 --> 00:16:21.540 align:middle line:84%
And it was almost
the death, you know,

00:16:21.540 --> 00:16:23.623 align:middle line:84%
it's like we were hearing
the death knell ringing.

00:16:23.623 --> 00:16:24.690 align:middle line:90%
The bell was ringing.

00:16:24.690 --> 00:16:28.530 align:middle line:84%
And that was a major
turning point there.

00:16:28.530 --> 00:16:32.820 align:middle line:84%
Either we went out of business
and we found something else

00:16:32.820 --> 00:16:34.470 align:middle line:90%
to do or we kept it going.

00:16:34.470 --> 00:16:37.080 align:middle line:84%
Well, somehow, just
through the graces

00:16:37.080 --> 00:16:40.290 align:middle line:84%
that were happening at the
time, we kept it together.

00:16:40.290 --> 00:16:41.820 align:middle line:10%
And we were able to--

00:16:41.820 --> 00:16:44.670 align:middle line:10%
it was right at the same
time, within a few months

00:16:44.670 --> 00:16:48.360 align:middle line:10%
the Public Broadcasting
satellite was being installed

00:16:48.360 --> 00:16:50.860 align:middle line:10%
to be available to public radio
stations around the country.

00:16:50.860 --> 00:16:54.690 align:middle line:10%
And so we basically were
able to put together

00:16:54.690 --> 00:16:55.950 align:middle line:10%
some programs for that.

00:16:55.950 --> 00:16:59.580 align:middle line:84%
And within a few months,
within maybe six months or so,

00:16:59.580 --> 00:17:02.310 align:middle line:84%
we were at the first conference,
first Public Radio conference

00:17:02.310 --> 00:17:05.730 align:middle line:84%
where the satellite
was actually-- the day

00:17:05.730 --> 00:17:08.490 align:middle line:90%
was the vernal equinox in 1980.

00:17:08.490 --> 00:17:10.050 align:middle line:90%
It was the spring equinox.

00:17:10.050 --> 00:17:12.930 align:middle line:84%
We were in Kansas City at
the Public Radio conference.

00:17:12.930 --> 00:17:16.380 align:middle line:84%
And our program was being beamed
on the satellite at that time.

00:17:16.380 --> 00:17:18.113 align:middle line:84%
And within a couple
of months of that,

00:17:18.113 --> 00:17:19.530 align:middle line:84%
we had 100 stations
that said they

00:17:19.530 --> 00:17:21.119 align:middle line:90%
wanted to carry New Dimensions.

00:17:21.119 --> 00:17:23.795 align:middle line:10%
So suddenly we had a national
audience and we were national.

00:17:23.795 --> 00:17:25.170 align:middle line:84%
And that made all
the difference.

00:17:25.170 --> 00:17:26.369 align:middle line:90%
And we went on.

00:17:26.369 --> 00:17:29.370 align:middle line:84%
And so that seeming
tragedy at the time,

00:17:29.370 --> 00:17:32.023 align:middle line:84%
which really put
us on a real downer

00:17:32.023 --> 00:17:34.440 align:middle line:84%
and looked like the destruction,
the potential destruction

00:17:34.440 --> 00:17:37.290 align:middle line:84%
of our work, turned
into a real blessing.

00:17:37.290 --> 00:17:40.930 align:middle line:84%
Because it forced us into a
situation where we had to say,

00:17:40.930 --> 00:17:44.362 align:middle line:84%
well, you know, we need
to do something else.

00:17:44.362 --> 00:17:45.320 align:middle line:90%
And that's what we did.

00:17:45.320 --> 00:17:48.180 align:middle line:84%
So we suddenly realized
that one station was not

00:17:48.180 --> 00:17:49.530 align:middle line:90%
going to make it for us.

00:17:49.530 --> 00:17:51.240 align:middle line:84%
And it didn't make it because
we were left without--

00:17:51.240 --> 00:17:52.770 align:middle line:84%
so we had to have
multiple stations.

00:17:52.770 --> 00:17:55.210 align:middle line:84%
So we went national
and it worked.

00:17:55.210 --> 00:17:57.140 align:middle line:90%
>> So you just kept your faith.

00:17:57.140 --> 00:17:58.360 align:middle line:90%
You kept persevering.

00:17:58.360 --> 00:18:01.470 align:middle line:90%
And you did not give up.

00:18:01.470 --> 00:18:02.310 align:middle line:90%
It was this idea--

00:18:02.310 --> 00:18:03.310 align:middle line:90%
>> Well, think about it.

00:18:03.310 --> 00:18:06.960 align:middle line:84%
A lot of the ideas and topics
and people we talked to

00:18:06.960 --> 00:18:08.270 align:middle line:90%
are people on the margins.

00:18:08.270 --> 00:18:09.830 align:middle line:90%
They're on the cutting edge.

00:18:09.830 --> 00:18:11.470 align:middle line:90%
They're not in the mainstream.

00:18:11.470 --> 00:18:13.220 align:middle line:84%
And we built that
network during the '80s,

00:18:13.220 --> 00:18:15.700 align:middle line:84%
during the Reagan era,
which was a very kind

00:18:15.700 --> 00:18:18.550 align:middle line:84%
of revisionist era going
back to conservative ideas.

00:18:18.550 --> 00:18:22.450 align:middle line:84%
And a lot of the ideas
were not in that milieu.

00:18:22.450 --> 00:18:24.430 align:middle line:84%
But we built a network
during that time.

00:18:24.430 --> 00:18:26.890 align:middle line:84%
Now we have over 300 stations
that carry our program

00:18:26.890 --> 00:18:28.270 align:middle line:90%
on a regular basis.

00:18:28.270 --> 00:18:30.490 align:middle line:84%
So we were basically
going up river,

00:18:30.490 --> 00:18:32.410 align:middle line:90%
against the tide at the time.

00:18:32.410 --> 00:18:35.110 align:middle line:84%
But still, you know, deep
underneath the surface

00:18:35.110 --> 00:18:36.970 align:middle line:84%
there's been a real
hunger, I think,

00:18:36.970 --> 00:18:39.970 align:middle line:84%
in our society in
America for the spiritual

00:18:39.970 --> 00:18:45.175 align:middle line:84%
and for a deeper message, one
that is hopeful and grounded.

00:18:45.175 --> 00:18:47.050 align:middle line:84%
And it's that message
that we try and deliver

00:18:47.050 --> 00:18:48.550 align:middle line:90%
on the airwaves.

00:18:48.550 --> 00:18:53.380 align:middle line:84%
>> I heard Jean Houston say,
mention that we're telling

00:18:53.380 --> 00:18:56.460 align:middle line:84%
stories for people who are
looking for the new story.

00:18:56.460 --> 00:18:58.010 align:middle line:90%
We're providing a curriculum.

00:18:58.010 --> 00:19:00.250 align:middle line:84%
And it seems to me
that you have certainly

00:19:00.250 --> 00:19:04.060 align:middle line:84%
been providing a curriculum
for the many, many people that

00:19:04.060 --> 00:19:08.800 align:middle line:84%
are looking for a new story
about life and how it can be.

00:19:08.800 --> 00:19:11.470 align:middle line:84%
>> And that's why it's so
exciting to have New Dimensions

00:19:11.470 --> 00:19:15.040 align:middle line:84%
radio hookup with the Wisdom
Network and the Wisdom Channel,

00:19:15.040 --> 00:19:19.250 align:middle line:84%
Wisdom Radio because you know,
Bill Turner's idea of a 24-hour

00:19:19.250 --> 00:19:23.650 align:middle line:84%
life-affirming television
channel and radio network is

00:19:23.650 --> 00:19:24.450 align:middle line:90%
a great idea.

00:19:24.450 --> 00:19:25.660 align:middle line:90%
>> And a new dimension.

00:19:25.660 --> 00:19:27.410 align:middle line:84%
>> And a new dimension
for New Dimensions.

00:19:27.410 --> 00:19:29.260 align:middle line:84%
And we're really happy
to be part of it.

00:19:29.260 --> 00:19:31.690 align:middle line:84%
And it's really an idea
whose time has come.

00:19:31.690 --> 00:19:33.430 align:middle line:90%
Because clearly when, you know--

00:19:33.430 --> 00:19:35.065 align:middle line:90%
you and I both travel a lot.

00:19:35.065 --> 00:19:37.190 align:middle line:84%
When I go into a city and
I turn on the television,

00:19:37.190 --> 00:19:39.648 align:middle line:84%
it's always amazing to me, you
know, you go in these cities

00:19:39.648 --> 00:19:43.180 align:middle line:84%
they have 60 or 70 choices, 60
or 70 choices on the television

00:19:43.180 --> 00:19:45.040 align:middle line:90%
and there's nothing to watch.

00:19:45.040 --> 00:19:46.670 align:middle line:90%
There's nothing worth seeing.

00:19:46.670 --> 00:19:49.600 align:middle line:84%
So the Wisdom Channel, I
think, is a real blessing

00:19:49.600 --> 00:19:54.310 align:middle line:84%
and a real important step
in this vast wasteland

